The paper deals with distributed algorithms for wireless networks, specifically in the SINR model. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also deals with wireless networks, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves information theory, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), respectively.
